Obituary



            HAZELGROVE, Bruce Reginald Jr., born January 2, 1929, died September 6, 2012. He was the son of Lucille M. and Bruce R. Hazelgrove Sr.; and was predeceased by his sister, Jane Lee H. Rollins. He is survived by his wife of 58 years, Mary McGrath Hazelgrove; his family, Mary Bruce Glaize and her husband, Phil, Sarah Hazelgrove, Bruce R. Hazelgrove III and his wife, Margaret, and Kevin Lee Beale and his wife, Beth. Bruce is survived by 10 grandchildren, Maggie, Lucy, Philip III and David Glaize, Burch, Bruce IV, Willie and Anne Stewart Hazelgrove and Thornton and Marshall Beale. He was a lifelong member of Centenary United Methodist Church, serving on numerous committees. Mr. Hazelgrove was educated in the Richmond City public schools and graduated from Thomas Jefferson High School where he served in the Cadet Corps attaining the rank of Captain of Company C and later Lieutenant Colonel and Battalion Commander. He was called to duty in the United States Army and was honorably discharged as a Sergeant. He joined the State Planters Bank of Commerce and Trust and served 31 years retiring from Crestar Bank. While at the bank, he completed the Virginia-Maryland School of Bank Management at the University of Virginia. The family will receive friends from 4 to 7 p.m. Sunday, September 9, at Bliley's-Central, 3801 Augusta Ave. A memorial service will be held 10 a.m. Monday, September 10, at Centenary United Methodist Church, 411 E. Grace St. In lieu of flowers, contributions may be made to the VMI Foundation, P.O. Box 932, Lexington, Virginia 24450.                    


